sVnews
p4
VA sedate and soulful &#8216;Eppadi Manam Thuninthatho&#8217; in Huseni  touched the audience. She then delivered a detailed Kalyani and sang a rare kriti, &#8216;Madhyam Dehi&#8217; of Vaanamamalai Jeeyar. This was followed by the rarely sung &#8216;Kalashavaardhijaam&#8217; in Ratnangi of Tyagaraja  and &#8216;Neekay&#8217; in Devamanohari of Poochi Srinivasa Iyengar. She took Khambodi  as the main piece and did full justice  to the raga, niraval and swaraprastara of the kriti, &#8216;Evari Maata.&#8217; She  concluded with a bhajan  and tillana.Nisha Rajagopal was ably supported by S.P.Anantha Padmanabha on the violin and R. Sankaranarayanan on the mridangam.
